Package: weightflow
Title: Declarative API for Staged Survey Weights
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Juan Pablo", "Ferreira", email = "juanpablo.ferreira@fcea.edu.uy", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Builds survey weights from design base weights by applying
    hierarchical adjustments (unknown eligibility, nonresponse and calibration)
    through a declarative, pipeable, tidymodels-style API. It computes weights
    only; it does not estimate variances. For inference, export the weights and
    use them with the 'survey' package.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports: stats, utils, graphics
Suggests: rpart, ranger
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE, roclets = c("rd"))
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
